<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1518,1653]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,445,1590,1617]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Taxonomic remarks.</emphasis>
Three 
<taxonomicName box="[524,721,1591,1617]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampeliscidae" genus="Haploops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[524,633,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Haploops</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
with only superior corneal lenses are morphologically close: 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liljeborg" authorityYear="1856" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampeliscidae" genus="Haploops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tubicola">H. tubicola</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shoemaker" authorityYear="1931" box="[257,379,1627,1652]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampeliscidae" genus="Haploops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosa">H. spinosa</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wildish and Dickinson" authorityYear="1982" box="[391,542,1627,1653]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampeliscidae" genus="Haploops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fundiensis">H. fundiensis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
These species can be separated mainly by the following characters:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1699,1869]" box="[151,1403,1699,1725]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liljeborg" authorityYear="1856" box="[151,277,1699,1725]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampeliscidae" genus="Haploops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tubicola">
<emphasis box="[151,277,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">H. tubicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: corneal lenses of great size; A2 = 2/3 body; Uropods 1 and 2 unequal sized rami, moderatly armed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1699,1869]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wildish and Dickinson" authorityYear="1982" box="[151,303,1735,1761]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampeliscidae" genus="Haploops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fundiensis">
<emphasis box="[151,303,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">H. fundiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: small corneal lenses; antennae short, A2 =1/3 body; Uropods 1 and 2 equal sized rami, weakly armed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1699,1869]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shoemaker" authorityYear="1931" box="[151,270,1807,1832]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampeliscidae" genus="Haploops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosa">
<emphasis box="[151,270,1807,1832]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">H. spinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: small corneal lenses; A2 length include between 1/3 and 1/2 body length; Uropods 1 and 2, rami of same size, strongly armed.
</paragraph>
